      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:3:19:2",
      "text": [
        " كُلُّ شَيْ‏ءٍ يَنْبُتُ فِي الْحَرَمِ فَهُوَ حَرَامٌ عَلَى النَّاسِ أَجْمَعِينَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Hammad, from Hareyz, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Everything growing in the Al-Harram, so it is Prohibited upon the entirety of the people’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from Hammad from Hariz who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘Everything that grows in al-Haram (the sacred area) is prohibited (restricted) for all people.’” "
        ]
      }
